news.title: IIT-Delhi team investigates Chintels Paradiso cave-in site
news.para: Last week, the district administration and the department of town and country planning (DTCP) appointed a structural engineer and a valuer to conduct an audit separate from the IIT-Delhi team and issued a work order. Both have started work.

news.title: Admin launches probe; colony is illegal, says Indore collector
news.para: According to IMC Commissioner Pratibha Pal, the civic body was responsible for extending infrastructure-related assistance to fire department.

news.title: Rustomjee Developers paid Rs 28 crore premium for land deal: Mumbai suburban collector
news.para: ​​BJP MLA Ashish Shelar had alleged that the transaction was a Rs 1,000-crore scam.

news.title: Builders liable to clear tax before flat registration: Kolkata civic body
news.para: A KMC assessment department official said a section of promoters kept the land owner with whom they enter into agreement to develop a residential building in the dark about the property tax payable to KMC during the intervening period.

news.title: Pre-1991 structure doesn't make new building in CRZ legal: NGT
news.para: The tribunal stated that it is not willing to accept the violator’s argument supporting the constructions because a structure existed at the location prior to 1991.

news.title: NGT slaps Rs 60 crore fine on Savfab Buildtech for flouting environment norms
news.para: The National Green Tribunal (NGT) has slapped a steep fine of Rs 60.23 crore on a developer for flouting various environment norms in its residential project in Ghaziabad.

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad development body launches fourth phase of demolition drive
news.para: HDUDA chief and a team of officials led the demolition drive in Unkal. This time around, HDUDA roped in police protection, deploying more police personnel.

news.title: Building plan must be displayed at entrance of new construction sites in Chennai
news.para: In an internal circular, chief engineer (planning) P Duraisamy has said presently not all constructions have building plans displayed at the site.

news.title: Refund flat buyers Rs 7 crore, builder cannot keep extending dates: MahaREAT
news.para: The tribunal set aside a January 2020 MahaRERA order, and said the revised date of possession on the MahaRERA website cannot be considered as the agreed date of possession and hence the buyers were entitled to refund with interest under RERA Act.

news.title: Nagpur: Part OC first denied citing 14 flaws, NIT now overlooks nine flaws
news.para: On Tuesday and Wednesday, TOI had reported NIT demolished 35 shops without providing tenants copy of part OC, violated its own norms in building permit, went against its own deadline, did not give any hearing to tenants, and did not ensure tenants had got possession of new shops etc.

news.title: Indore: Five persons booked for developing illegal colony on government land
news.para: The accused have been identified as Amarchand, a resident of Simrol, Sumit Rajoriya, Kamal, Sandeep Bijoriya, and Punamchand - all residents of Asrawad Khurd.

news.title: WeWork turns profitable, reports around 40% year-on-year growth
news.para: The Bengaluru-based company, which started operations five years ago, reported an operating profit margin of Rs 25 crore for January-March, with around 40% year-on-year growth. The co-working operator reported revenue of Rs 800 crore for 2021.

news.title: Telangana plans two more recycling plants to handle construction waste
news.para: Only two units, each with 500 tonnes per day capacity, operate for construction waste whereas thousands of tonnes are produced every day, according to a report submitted by the Telangana government in National Green Tribunal on municipal solid waste management.

news.title: HC issues notice to Maharashtra real estate tribunal
news.para: The high court called for a response from the registrar of the Maharashtra Real Estate Appellate Tribunal and to consider whether matters arising from Goa can be heard by the Tribunal virtually.

news.title: Mumbai: Two weeks after FIR, society transfers membership to home buyer
news.para: Sengupta-Das, a 51-year-old widow and cancer survivor, had bought a 2BHK flat in the society for Rs 4.15 crore in February 2021, and moved in with her two children in July 2021.
